<HL>
   Buffton Plans to Sell Assets
</HL>
<DATE>
12/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE 3
</SO>
<CO>
   BFX
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)
</IN>
<LP>
   FORT WORTH, Texas -- Buffton Corp. said it has signed a
letter of intent to sell the assets of National Pipe Co. of
Vestal, New York, to the Regency Group of Houston for
approximately $14 million.
   The manufacturer of avionic, electronic and plastic
products said the money will be used to reduce bank debt.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Closing of the transaction, which must be approved by
Buffton's board, is scheduled for Jan. 31.
</TEXT>
